cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 80 mi NNW of the western tip of Cuba

motion.direction: Nearly stationary (expected to drift slowly north tonight)

cyclone.trajectory: Forecast to drift, then move slowly northward through the east-central Gulf, turning northeast toward the Florida Gulf Coast late Thursday and crossing northern Florida into the Atlantic Saturday
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Gulf Coast (likely north of Tampa/Cedar Key area)

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical Storm Watch in effect only for portions of western Cuba (La Habana through Isle of Youth)
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Western Cuba, South Florida, the Florida Keys, entire Florida Gulf Coast, portions of north Florida and southeast Georgia
weather_observation.wind: Breezy conditions; tropical-storm-force winds unlikely (≤3% chance)
weather_observation.storm_surge: No significant surge expected along the northeast Florida Atlantic coast
weather_observation.rainfall: 1–3 inches of rain possible Friday–Saturday as the storm crosses the peninsula
weather_observation.other_hazards: Rough surf and rip currents along northeast Florida beaches late week
